column5: ...today it was discovered that my carb boots are shot. I have decided on a new mode of transportation on the lake! http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MN9rW__S3Gk
Great use for something that gets used twice a year!! Good one!!! Time to retire your old sled. What's next after the carb boots, the track, etc...etc...
Brilliant!  That tiny thing has some serious towing power haha
dang, I was telling Lloyd I wanted to make an ice walker from one of them, to pull my portable hut out when we can't use skidoos
it's an '02, but it only has 1200 miles!  i can't retire that yet!

They have boots at Canadian tire in the rain suit isle for 9.99?  Not sure if this helps you out any!  It may keep the carbs dry, and insulated.  Just trying to make it better.  Sorry about the luck these days.  1200 miles?  Geez.
